/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-01.md:178:   mathematical operability first, Tao-sensitivity second.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:5:This chain is attacking the right high-upside question, but it is structurally at risk of confusing an algebraic rewrite with a usable estimate. The central analogy to SQG is weaker than the chain admits: in SQG, the first-order commutator is tied to scalar transport and a linear constitutive law, while in NS the Lamb-vector / vorticity / Helmholtz forms are mostly equivalent repackagings of the same quadratic vector interaction. Unless the chain screens candidates at the level of the actual localized or truncated estimate that matters, it can spend several steps rediscovering textbook identities and then either overclaim a negative result or drift into Chain 03's Beltrami geometry.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:13:- The hidden assumption is that a side-by-side comparison across velocity, vorticity, Lamb-vector, and Helmholtz-projected forms can reveal a genuinely new "slot" for SQG-style cancellation. That is not obvious. These are equivalent formulations before truncation/localization, and the mission-context obstruction is precisely that the bad behavior appears after truncation/localization.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:14:- The step risks re-deriving facts the mission already treats as established: scalar truncation survives in SQG, vector truncation does not in NS; the vorticity route still lands at the same `beta = 4/3` barrier; Beltrami cancellation is exact but fragile. If the comparison matrix just restates those points, Step 1 produces paperwork, not progress.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:27:- Scale counting is not enough. A symbol can look first-order under naive counting and still fail once the relevant truncation, commutator, or nonlocal pressure reconstruction is applied. This step needs estimate-level testing, not just identity-level algebra.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:28:- There is prior-art overlap here that the chain underplays. The mission context already says the vorticity formulation does not beat the barrier. So one of the main advertised candidate formulations already comes with a strong negative prior.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:36:- Testing exact Beltrami flows is a weak stress test for an allegedly generic NS mechanism. Exact Beltrami is a highly nongeneric symmetry class where the Lamb vector vanishes by design. Success there proves almost nothing.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:37:- The mission context already records the crucial negative fact: the Beltrami-based cancellation does not survive even very small perturbations from alignment. That means Step 3 is in danger of rediscovering an established fragility rather than testing a genuinely open point.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:38:- "Small perturbations away from Beltrami alignment" is underspecified. Small in `L^2`, `H^1`, direction field, or a pointwise angle deficit? These are mathematically very different. Without fixing the perturbation metric, the stress test is not interpretable.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:40:- This step overlaps heavily with Chain 03. Once the test object becomes "Beltrami alignment plus perturbations," the chain has drifted from algebraic reformulation into geometry-first fragility analysis. That weakens the claim that Chain 02 is meaningfully distinct.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:42:Concrete failure mode: Step 3 may produce an inequality that looks favorable in an exact or nearly exact Beltrami regime, then collapse outside that regime. At that point the chain has not found an SQG-type mechanism; it has merely recovered the known statement that special alignment depletes the nonlinearity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:44:### Step 4 - Apply the Tao filter and close the chain
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:46:Including the Tao filter is correct, but putting it last is a structural mistake.
