/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/refined/chain-02.md:53:- Action: restore full dyadic shell summation, angular multiplicity, and all mixed-helicity interactions, and calculate whether the Step 3 gain survives with positive margin.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/refined/chain-02.md:54:- Action: if the theorem endpoint needs localization, add the corresponding cutoff, commutator, local-energy, or profile-decomposition losses and test whether the mechanism is stable under that reconstruction.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/refined/chain-02.md:55:- Action: perturb away from exactly favorable helicity or resonance classes and determine whether the gain reflects true structure or only a narrow regime artifact.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/refined/chain-02.md:56:- Action: classify failure precisely as effect-size insufficiency, shell-summation collapse, angular-multiplicity collapse, mixed-helicity collapse, localization collapse, or regime-only signal.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:5:The attack is mostly correct about where this branch is weak. The original chain already has two real strengths: it insists on the full stretching term `S omega . omega`, and it refuses to hide the pressure Hessian. But the attack correctly identifies that the chain remains too permissive before Step 4, checks novelty too late, and risks treating "find the right observable" as a live default rather than as a claim that must itself be screened early.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:14:The attack is right that a tensor ledger is bookkeeping, not leverage, and that bookkeeping the pressure debt is not the same as paying it. It is also right that a single frozen representation would risk coordinate bias. But fixing a small representation set remains good discipline if the chain requires any claimed mechanism to survive a second natural formulation rather than relying on just one.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:24:The original Tao screen is underdefined, and the attack is right that labels like sign coupling or cancellation are not yet criteria. The refinement should demote Tao-sensitivity to secondary evidence after definability, invariance near degeneracy, and contradiction power are already established. The eigenvalue-degeneracy point is also decisive enough that it must be handled before any positive sales pitch.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:29:The attack correctly identifies this as the decisive step and the most likely collapse point. The original chain knows that the pressure debt may be the same order as the asset, but it lets earlier steps remain too qualitative. The refinement should force a full-mechanism control attempt earlier and require the first missing lemma to be named precisely once the real estimate is written down.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:34:The novelty check is indeed too late in the original version. In a literature-heavy area like stretching, alignment, and pressure-Hessian geometry, overlap must be audited before candidate selection hardens. The attack is also right that theorem-shaped propositions can disguise circularity unless the missing theorem is proved to be narrower than full regularity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:54:The original kill conditions are honest but too interpretive. The refinement should replace broad phrases with more operational failure types: overlap collapse, representation dependence, degeneracy collapse, only-correlation-without-control, pressure debt same-order nonclosure, or missing lemma equivalent to the whole problem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:68:- Demote Tao-sensitivity from main gate to secondary support.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-03.md:75:Most likely presentable result: a sharp obstruction memo showing that tensor-level alignment or misalignment data remains informative but non-coercive once representation dependence, eigenvalue degeneracy, and full pressure-Hessian debt are charged honestly.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/planner-chains/chain-03.md:3:## Central Premise
