/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:105:As a falsification program for the Lorentz or weak-type lead named in the mission context, this chain is good. As a serious positive route beyond De Giorgi, it is weak. The main reason is not that endpoint ideas are impossible; it is that this chain never identifies a Navier-Stokes-specific mechanism that weak-type packaging would carry. Without that, it is mostly an audit of whether generic endpoint harmonic analysis can be made to look more structural than it is.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:107:The most likely earned output is a negative result of the form: once De Giorgi recursion is forbidden, the remaining weak-type package either collapses under localization, reduces to strong-type control, or stays inside Tao-compatible generic harmonic analysis. That would still be useful. But it means the chain should be viewed primarily as a cleanup operation on one lingering mission lead, not as a strong forward route to regularity.
